  "description": "QuickBooks is accounting software developed by Intuit, first released in 1992 [citation needed]. It\u0026rsquo;s the most widely used small-business accounting software in the United States [citation needed].\n¶What It Does QuickBooks handles invoicing, expense tracking, bank reconciliation, inventory, and tax preparation integration (via TurboTax). Payroll is available as an add-on. It comes in two forms: QuickBooks Online (cloud, subscription-based) and QuickBooks Desktop (locally installed, though Intuit has been phasing this toward cloud).\n",
